## Skills

The following skills are installed in `~/.claude/skills/`:

### SDD Workflow
- `sdd-orchestrator` ‚Äî **Entry point**: run `/sdd-new`, `/sdd-ff`, or `/sdd-continue` to start
- `sdd-init` ‚Äî Initialize SDD context in a project
- `sdd-explore` ‚Äî Investigate ideas before committing to a change
- `sdd-clarify` ‚Äî Clarify requirements and confirm scope before proposing (semi-mandatory)
- `sdd-propose` ‚Äî Create a change proposal with intent, scope, and approach
- `sdd-spec` ‚Äî Write specifications with Given/When/Then scenarios
- `sdd-design` ‚Äî Write technical design document with architecture decisions
- `sdd-tasks` ‚Äî Break down a change into a numbered implementation checklist
- `sdd-apply` ‚Äî Implement tasks from the change following specs and design
- `sdd-verify` ‚Äî Validate that implementation matches specs, design, and tasks
- `sdd-qa` ‚Äî QA phase: auto-execute tests, generate manual checklist for the developer
- `sdd-archive` ‚Äî Archive a completed change and sync delta specs
- `sdd-onboard` ‚Äî Guided end-to-end walkthrough of the full SDD workflow

### Utilities
- `engram-memory` ‚Äî Persistent memory protocol (protocol is inlined below by default ‚Äî no skill load needed)
- `branch-pr` ‚Äî PR creation workflow following issue-first enforcement
- `issue-creation` ‚Äî GitHub issue creation workflow
- `judgment-day` ‚Äî Parallel adversarial review: two blind judge sub-agents
- `skill-creator` ‚Äî Create new AI agent skills following the Agent Skills spec
- `skill-registry` ‚Äî Create or update the skill registry for the current project

### Domain
- `zoho-deluge` ‚Äî Zoho Deluge coding standard: statement optimization, security, scalability

**Auto-trigger rule**: When the user asks to write, review, or refactor Zoho Deluge code ‚Äî including `.dg` or `.ds` files, Creator functions, CRM workflows, or any Zoho automation ‚Äî invoke the `zoho-deluge` skill with the Skill tool BEFORE writing any code. Do not skip this step.

